# MPSE = My Portable Shell Environment

The idea is to have a gittree off your HOME directory that contains
all your portable stuff, and you make symlinks into this tree, change
the path etc.


to install:
  cd $HOME
  git clone https://github.com/teuben/teunix

potential commands (but careful overwritting old ones)

cd Env
cp dotcshrc ../.cshrc		(or cat >>)
cp dotemacs ../.emacs
(cd ..; ln -s Env/emacs)
(cd ..; ln -s Env/bin)




##  2018:

From your home directory:

1. add this to your .bashrc (linux) or .bash_profile (mac)

   if [ -f ~/teunix/Env/aliases.sh ]; then
       . ~/teunix/Env/aliases.sh
   fi

2. add this to your .cshrc file

   if ( -e ~/teunix/Env/aliases.csh ) then
      source ~/teunix/Env/aliases.csh
   endif


2. emacs: make sure there is no existing .emacs file

   ln -s teunix/Env/dotemacs .emacs
